{{Orphan|date=August 2015}}
'''Leavisism''' is a form of [[literary studies]] named after [[F. R. Leavis]]. Leavis was greatly influenced by [[Matthew Arnold]] and they share the notion that culture is the high point in civilization and concern of an educated minority.<ref>The Cultural Studies Reader by Simon During, 1999</ref> Leavis argues that prior to industrial revolution England had an authentic culture of the educated elite. For Leavis it was a golden age of an organic community with a lived culture of Folk-song and Folk-dance.<ref>Cultural Studies: Theory and Practice by Chris Barker, 12 Dec 2011</ref>
